%group,name="Problem 1",description="Exchange elements 3."
========================================================================================================

Problem 1

Define a procedure named "exchangeElements3" that
has a single parameter named "list". The procedure
should accept a list as an argument. A "Check"
procedure should be used to make sure that the
argument is a list.

The procedure should return a new list that
contains the first element in the argument list
exchanged with the last element in the argument
list.

Hint: Make a copy of the argument list first (a
While loop can be used for this), then modify the
copy before returning it. Remember lists can be
modified in place like this:

In> lst := ["a","b","c"]
Result: ["a","b","c"]

In> lst[1] := "x"
Result: True

In> lst
Result: ["x","b","c"]


You can test your procedure with the following
code:

[
    exchangeElements3(["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"]),
    exchangeElements3(["a","b","c","d","e","f","g"]),
];

Result: [["H","B","C","D","E","F","G","A"],["g","b","c","d","e","f","a"]]


%mathpiper,name="Problem 1",subtype="problem",unassign_all="true",truncate="1000",timeout="5000"

Procedure("exchangeElements3", ["list"])
{
    Local(resultList, index, listLength);
    
    Check(List?(list), "The argument must be a list.");
    
    resultList := [];
    
    index := 1;
    
    listLength := Length(list);
    
    While(index <=? listLength)
    {        
        Append!(resultList, list[index]);
        
        If(index =? 1)
        {
            resultList[1] := list[listLength];
        }
        
        Else If(index =? listLength)
        {
            resultList[listLength] := list[1];
        }
        
        index +:= 1;
    }
    
    resultList;
}

[
    exchangeElements3(["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"]),
    exchangeElements3(["a","b","c","d","e","f","g"]),
];

//Result: [["H","B","C","D","E","F","G","A"],["g","b","c","d","e","f","a"]]


%/mathpiper

